injury /ˈɪndʒərɪ/

(injuries) 

1. N-VAR An injury is damage done to a person's or an animal's body. 伤害; 损害 

例： Four police officers sustained serious injuries in the explosion. 四名警官在爆炸中受了重伤。 

2. N-VAR If someone suffers injury to their feelings, they are badly upset by something. If they suffer injury to their reputation, their reputation is seriously harmed. (对感情或名誉等的) 伤害 [法律] 

例： She was awarded $3,500 for injury to her feelings. 她获得了3500美元的精神损伤费。 

3. to add insult to injury→see insult

